    </div>

    <h3>Vitamin B6: The Essential Cofactor for 5-HTP Conversion</h3>

    <p>The enzyme that converts 5-HTP to serotonin — aromatic amino acid decarboxylase (AADC) — requires pyridoxal-5-phosphate (the active form of vitamin B6) as a cofactor. Without adequate B6, 5-HTP supplementation may be less effective because the conversion enzyme cannot function optimally. Products that include B6 alongside 5-HTP provide more complete serotonin synthesis support. This is why our top-ranked products all include vitamin B6.</p>

