    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About 5-HTP Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is 5-HTP and how does it work?</summary><p>5-HTP is the direct precursor to serotonin. It crosses the BBB efficiently and is converted to serotonin in one enzymatic step, supporting mood, sleep, and appetite regulation.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How much 5-HTP should I take?</summary><p>50-200mg daily. Start at 50mg and increase gradually. For mood: divided doses. For sleep: 100-200mg 30-60 min before bed.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can 5-HTP help with sleep?</summary><p>Yes — serotonin converts to melatonin in the pineal gland. 5-HTP + GABA reduced sleep latency by 19 minutes and increased duration by 45 minutes.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take 5-HTP with antidepressants?</summary><p>NO. Never combine with SSRIs, SNRIs, MAOIs, or triptans — risk of serotonin syndrome, a potentially fatal condition. Consult your physician.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What are the side effects of 5-HTP?</summary><p>Most common: nausea, diarrhea (dose-dependent, reduced by taking with food). Less common: vivid dreams, drowsiness. Start low and increase gradually.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Is 5-HTP better than tryptophan?</summary><p>Yes for serotonin boosting — 5-HTP bypasses the rate-limiting conversion step and crosses the BBB without amino acid competition.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>When should I take 5-HTP gummies?</summary><p>For mood: morning or divided. For sleep: 30-60 min before bed. For appetite: 30 min before meals. A small carb snack may enhance efficacy.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How long does 5-HTP take to work?</summary><p>Sleep: within 1 week. Mood: 2-4 weeks. Appetite: 4-8 weeks. Consistent daily use is more effective than sporadic dosing.</p></details>

    <div class="warn-box"><span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span><p><strong>CRITICAL:</strong> 5-HTP must NEVER be combined with serotonergic medications (SSRIs, SNRIs, MAOIs, triptans, tramadol). Serotonin syndrome can be fatal. If you take any prescription medication, consult your physician before starting 5-HTP. Pregnant and nursing women should not take 5-HTP. Long-term use exceeding 3-6 months should be monitored by a healthcare provider.</p></div>

